  <title>Leprosy Mission : Dhaka Community based rehabilitation</title>
  <description>The project will aim to provide an improved quality of life for people with leprosy related disabilities and people with physical disabilities with a focus on women. Self help groups for people with disabilities will be given training in income generating activities and will have their capacity developed to enable them to access rights and entitlements to government health services and to improve access to education for their children. The project has received Scottish Government support since 2010 through the South Asia development fund.</description>
